      "content": "You are right to be cautious, as the theory doesn't always perfectly align with real-world microeconomics. The core issue is that the demand increase from higher wages is not guaranteed to perfectly offset the cost increase from mandated pay hikes. Ultimately, the market will adjust, and if businesses raise prices too sharply, they risk losing price-sensitive customers, which is a very real risk.",
